Definition.WordDefinition: biochemical \bi`o*chem"ic*al\ n. a chemical substance produced by a living organism, or such a substance produced synthetically. [WordNet 1.5]
biochemical adj : of or relating to biochemistry; involving chemical processes in living organisms
